This is a pilot study and we are exploring the feasibility of running a trained peer mentored intervention to reduce CVD risk at workplaces.The UK-MRC/ Wellcome trust/ DFID is the principle source of funding for this development.</gtr:description><gtr:id>0069F91C-BB86-4648-A2B7-DC667DB88056</gtr:id><gtr:impact>The first set of peer mentors at one workplace in India have been trained. Anecdotal evidence suggests positive lifestyle changes among the mentors and their family members.</gtr:impact><gtr:outcomeId>56efe4d7c31080.75126543</gtr:outcomeId><gtr:stage>Initial development</gtr:stage><gtr:status>Under active development/distribution</gtr:status><gtr:title>Peer mentoring for risk reduction</gtr:title><gtr:type>Preventative Intervention - Physical/Biological risk modification</gtr:type><gtr:yearDevCompleted>2016</gtr:yearDevCompleted></gtr:productOutput></gtr:productOutputs><gtr:researchDatabaseAndModelOutputs><gtr:researchDatabaseAndModelOutput><gtr:description>We are using the PROMASYS database management system for managing data in the PROGRESS study. We have used this database management system to create the data collection forms, build in edit checks and to provide remote access to our collaborators in Bangladesh and Sri Lanka to manage their data.</gtr:description><gtr:id>A84D4B39-B338-4B00-9CF5-F653C204ACDF</gtr:id><gtr:impact>Since the project is ongoing, this is yet to have impact</gtr:impact><gtr:outcomeId>56efe0ea435617.34828452</gtr:outcomeId><gtr:providedToOthers>false</gtr:providedToOthers><gtr:title>PROMASYS</gtr:title><gtr:type>Database/Collection of data</gtr:type></gtr:researchDatabaseAndModelOutput></gtr:researchDatabaseAndModelOutputs><gtr:researchMaterialOutputs><gtr:researchMaterialOutput><gtr:description>INTRODUCTION AND Purpose: since the intervention was new to the Peer mentors, we had a refresher training for the peer mentors at both the work sites in India &amp;amp; Bangladesh to help them to understand better the intervention, target set